From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: Fix cpuid.h cross-compilation check for x86 targets

When cross-compiling glibc for x86, the cpuid.h header check uses
ac_fn_c_check_header_mongrel which includes <stdio.h> in the test
program. Since glibc itself provides <stdio.h>, it is not yet available
during the start-files stage of cross-compilation, causing the check
to falsely fail.

Switch to ac_fn_c_check_header_compile with an empty includes list,
since cpuid.h is a standalone GCC internal header with no dependencies.

--- a/sysdeps/i386/configure
+++ b/sysdeps/i386/configure
@@ -632,7 +632,7 @@
 done


-ac_fn_c_check_header_mongrel "$LINENO" "cpuid.h" "ac_cv_header_cpuid_h" "$ac_includes_default"
+ac_fn_c_check_header_compile "$LINENO" "cpuid.h" "ac_cv_header_cpuid_h" ""
 if test "x$ac_cv_header_cpuid_h" = xyes; then :

 else
